<p>How about  Jobs chart.   Here, just take the one made up for Chris's show a week or so ago:  <a href="http://johnmesserly.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/job-growth-needed-to-get-back-to-2008-emplormen-upwchris201302_03t.jpg">We won't get back to 2008 employment until 2020</a>.  And even if we do that, that does not mean back to the same employment strength we had in 2008.  Real restoration of strength to 2008 levels means both restoring the same employment to population ratio, and restoring the the income from those jobs to the same level.</p>
<p>Now, here is the super depressing point.  Even though the real growth in jobs as compared to population is negative, the job growth at high incomes are negative, and all the job growth is at the low income jobs.  Take a look at <a href="http://johnmesserly.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/declining-employment-skills-copy.jpg">this chart.</a></p>
<p>It's a bad, bad scene folks.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:74174302,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3666295&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;16951837&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;johnmesserly&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c74174302" title="Link to this comment">#2</a> - Wed Feb 13, 2013 3:19 PM EST</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c74174430"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:74174430,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-davenguyen501&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Dave Nguyen&quot;}"></div><a name="star2"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star3" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://fb-davenguyen501.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=nullBE81554A-AA1D-C710-F62D-29BC1D78DF53.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://fb-davenguyen501.newsvine.com/">Dave Nguyen</a></div></div><div id="commentText_74174430" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I wonder how different that chart would be if we weren't so concerned with reducing a 0% interest debt..</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:74174430,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3666295&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;16951837&quot;,&